author: PETER SBLENDORIO
title: ‘Power Rangers’ star pleads guilty to voluntary manslaughter
text:
‘Power Rangers’ star Ricardo Medina Jr. pleads guilty to voluntary manslaughter in roommate’s killing ‘Power Rangers’ star pleads guilty to voluntary manslaughter NEW YORK DAILY NEWS   4:52 PM 
A former "Power Rangers” actor pleaded guilty in the killing of his roommate, the Los Angeles District Attorney's office announced. 
Ricardo Medina Jr. — who played the Red Power Ranger — pleaded guilty to a felony count of voluntary manslaughter, admitting an allegation of using a sword in his roommate's killing. 
The 38-year-old will return for sentencing on March 30, and he faces six years in prison. Ricardo Medina Jr. plead guilty to voluntary manslaughter. (Albert L. Ortega/Getty Images) 
The altercation between Medina and Josh Sutter, his roommate at the time, occurred on Jan. 31, 2015. They had gotten into a dispute regarding the actor's girlfriend, according to Thursday's press announcement.
